{
  "Battle in the Mind": {
    rank: 2,
    type: "Combat",
    approach: "Fortune",
    skill: null,
    flavor: "An elite who has survived enough engagements learns to recognize the signals an opponent does not intend to reveal: the posture, the hesitation, the split-second flicker of the eyes. By the time the first shot is fired, a plan is already in motion.",
    description: """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>When you make an Initiative check for a duel using your Fortune Approach, you may spend (op) in the following way:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Fortune (op):</strong> Name two approaches. Your opponent must choose one, and cannot select it as their posture during their first turn of the duel.</li>
        <li><strong>Fortune (op)+:</strong> Choose a technique category. Learn one of your opponent's known techniques of that category (chosen by the opponent) per (op) spent this way.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  "Shoot to Maim": {
    rank: 1,
    type: "Combat",
    approach: "Precision",
    skill: null,
    flavor: "Not every shot is meant to kill. A well-placed round to the knee, shoulder, or hand achieves something a lethal shot cannot: it leaves the opponent present, suffering, and in the way.",
    description: """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>While you perform an Attack action check, you may spend (op) as follows:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Precision (op)(op):</strong> Choose one of the following conditions: Bleeding, Dazed, Disoriented, Prone. If this check inflicts that condition on one or more targets, those targets cannot remove that condition until the end of your next turn.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  "Last Stand": {
    rank: 2,
    type: "Combat",
    approach: "Power",
    skill: null,
    flavor: "A fighter who is wounded but still standing is not a weakened threat. They are a desperate one. Pain strips away restraint, and what remains is something faster, uglier, and harder to predict than anything training produces.",
    description: """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>When you make a check to resist a critical strike during a skirmish, if you are Enraged and not Incapacitated, you may spend (op) in the following way:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Power (op)+:</strong> Choose one of your unarmed profiles or a readied improvised weapon. Each other character at range 0–1 with vigilance lower than or equal to (op) spent this way suffers physical damage equal to the base damage of your unarmed profile plus 1 for each (op) spent in excess of their vigilance.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  "Cleaving Strike": {
    rank: 3,
    type: "Combat",
    approach: null,
    skill: null,
    flavor: "Ranged combat doctrine dominates modern engagements for good reason. But veterans who have survived close-quarters fighting know that a skilled blade user occupies a threat category of their own. Bullets shred flesh and damage metal. Only a blade can cleave an arm from its frame.",
    description: """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>When you make an Attack action check with a melee weapon, you may spend (op) in the following way:</p>
