      </ul>
    """
  },
  "Improvised Hazard": {
    rank: 1,
    type: "Street",
    approach: "Swiftness",
    skill: "Survival",
    flavor: "Ideal conditions mean overwhelming force, clear sightlines, and perfect positioning. Ideal conditions are rare. A smart operative learns to use whatever is at hand: broken glass cuts feet, a kicked-over shelf forces a detour, and a cloud of dust blinds just as well as any deployment.",
    description: """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>As a Movement and Scheme action, you may make a <strong>TN 2 Survival (Swiftness)</strong> check targeting one position at range 1–2.</p>
